n-water swimming and triathlon events in a spectacular setting in the middle of the city.\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2546, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wastewater infrastructure\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2383}, {\"ngram\": \"sewage\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2401}, {\"ngram\": \"an ambitious plan\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2422}, {\"ngram\": \"the river and host open-water swimming and triathlon events\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2494}, {\"ngram\": \"a spectacular setting\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2519}, {\"ngram\": \"the middle\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2533}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 2537, \"to\": 2545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 president Tony Estanguet, Paris mayor Anne Hidalgo and Marc Guillaume, the top government official for the Paris region, all took a dip on 17 July to prove the Seine's water cleanliness had improved.\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2548, \"end\": 2558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9647067616570485e-22, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 2585, \"end\": 2590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1799212704709366e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2597, \"end\": 2609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"tex